  "description": [
    "THE BROWNING CHIEF John E Davies Editor and Owner A weekly newspaper published every Friday at Browning Glacier County Montana Entered as 2nd class matter July 15 1931 at the postoffice at Browning Mqgjana under act of March 3 1879 Subscription 200 year in advance FIGHTING FOR PEACE A good deal of comment on re cent events in Korea assumes a change in United Nations or United States policy General Bradleys visit and his remark that UN forces are capable of winning a successful military conclusion have been interpret ed as announcing a decision to quit fooling with truce talks and drive to the Yalu Increas ing activity on the front appears to support this view Yet it is not supported by the basic situation in Korea For months UN policy has followed a middle course of limited war in Korea It largely caused the dismissal of MacArthur and was maintained against all the press ures that developed after the general aired his case at home It led to the truce talks and has not been formally abandoned PSALE M ANNUAL BIG SAVINGS ON Dorothy Gray Cleansing Creams n OC Solon Cold Croon Reg 225 80 I far normal ikin"
  ],
